                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261207-235-off1368 t18261207-235-crimeloc1370"></join>. On the 8th of December, at six o'clock in the evening, I was alarmed by one of the workmen; we got on the top of the house with a ladder, and found the prisoner there, with this roll of lead by his side; it appeared fresh cut; he had two knives; I did not know him before; it is an unfinished house.</p>
               <p>GEORGE WATKINS. I belong to this house - this lead was on the roof - the prisoner is a stranger.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18261207-235-person1324">
                  THOMAS 
                  WOOD
